==========
#Start in directory terminal
vim file.txt #opens file.txt in vim
#vim starts in command mode, press "i" to edit, vim has 4 modes
#press esc to enter command mode again
:wq #type :w (write) and q(quit to save and quit)
:q #to quit vim without saving
:[range]s/{pattern}/{string}/[flags] #find and replace text in vim
#How to undo: To undo a change in Vim, press u in command mode. 
#To redo, press CTRL + R. 
#You can prepend a number (n) with u to undo n times. for example, 2u will undo 2 times. To list the available undo options, type :undolist in command mode.





